<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for Tindien"></A>  &nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=7&t=001608&reply_num=000000&u=00008251"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=7&t=001608&replyto=000000"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I've come to a new understanding about the Magician class in the past few days.  Ive done a lot of posting, and a lot of reading about the "new" exp penalty they just figured out.  <P>Apparently, Magicians see themselves primarily as pet wielders, and secondarily(or thirdly) as nukers.  When talking about the exp penalty, they conveniently leave out all thoughts of nukes, and only mention the pet...ie:  If their pet cant outdamage every tank in group, they arent effective.  If their pet can outdamage all tanks at their own level, its not fair to be penalized.  With Magicians being the closest class to Wizard, Its obvious that comparing our spells to them is rediculous.  Magicians wield pets foremost, and cast nukes if they think about it.<P>So here's what I say.  Without stepping on Magicians toes, Wizards can become primarily nukers, and secondarily pet wielders.  Why not?  I didnt even know before a few weeks ago that mage pets were as powerful as they are.  And looking at how close mage nukes come to wizard nukes, I think we(wizards) deserve some serious class balancing to keep up.  <P>If Wizards got half as many nuke spells as magicians get pet spells, we'd be...well...an efficient nuking class.  But, since that doesnt fit "The Vision"(little TM sign), there must be another way.  Ive already suggested more nukes per level, and more powerful ones thatl let us keep up with Druids, but we need something else to become "uber."  <P>So Wizards should start getting Flaming Swords of Xuzl starting at lvl 30.  A cool looking flaming sword, with 50hps, thatl do 20dmg a hit.  Itl be like a paladin with a really weak sword and no health.  But, it balances us with mages.  It gives Wizards something that does dmg while we sit around and wait to nuke, and it also in no way betters our ability to solo.  Heck, make it cost a peridot to summon....but they shouldnt die after each fight.  Instead, this flaming sword should be just like a mage pet, so long as we can control its aggro it wont die.  Remember, Wizards aren't the masters of damage, we're the masters of Aggro. <P>And about familiars?  Its a good idea in practice, but at lvl 34 familiars do almost nothing.  Just resists, which I dont feel I need for OT.  Personally, id much rather have a flaming sword than one more tic of mana regen at lvl 50.  But thats just me. <P>Flame On!
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
