<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Tindien, if you say we (mages) leave out all thoughts about nuking when talking about the pet exp penalty, I have to tell you that in your comparison you conveniently leave out all fantastic defensive/utility spells wizards get  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Actually, mages ARE primarily pet wielders. We achieve most of our damage with our pets, and only nuke to support it (or to get all exp from a kill).<P>A comparison:<BR>- Wizard catches four mobs, quad kites them around, and has to med up after that.<BR>- Mage takes on four single mobs one after the other (pet tanking and mage supporting with a few nukes), after that he's oom too and needs to med up as well.<P>So you see, mages aren't really that more effective (we may have it easier at levels below 50). They also get only half the exp in the above example (no, mages cannot outdamage their pets continually with nukes). And to complete the comparison, wizards can do their tactic all the way to 60 if they like. Mages cant do theirs anymore past somewhere in the low 50's.<P>About wizards getting (damage doing) pets...I think this doesnt fit with the role of the wizard, who does all with his own power (but thats my opinion of course).<P>To come back to the pet exp penalty...the real problem mages see with this is that while we bring good damage output to groups, we also bring some risk (mez breaking pets, ...). Now we hear that we also bring a possible exp penalty to the group! That's what we worry about, because who would take a pet class in the group now if a non-pet class is available?
</FONT>
