<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
You know, after reading this thread, I'm actually shocked. Why are 2 so inherently obvious different classes bickering about being equal? Mages SHOULD NOT be equal to us in damage. Take a look at your spell line mages...<P>1) Pets. With out doubt one of the two lines of spells that sets you apart from every other class. Whether you consider it your primary or secondary form of damage output is up to you.<P>2) Nukes. You have nukes that appear to be second only in strength to those of the wizards.<P>3) Summons. The other line of spells that defines you as a class. You have an entire line of spells devoted to keeping yourself, and your group, if not well equipped, equipped. You can summon food, water, bags, weapons, and now with Luclin you even summon water. Not to mention magical items which are clickable for buff spells.<P>4) Damage shields. You do still have some of the best damage shields in the game.<P>5) Debuffs. You have spells meant to lower the resistance of your enemies to your magical spells.<P>Just looking at your spell line, you are not meant to be as damaging as a wizard in combat, most likely not even close, yet you are. On top of that, you also have a pet to tank for you (And I personally find that my mages pet is better than root, it's a root/DOT). You are a class that has the ability to solo very well from lvl 4 beyond. Your role in a group is not meant to be a damage dealer. You're there to debuff, and and add some (alot of) extra damage. At 60 you best nuke hits for less than 200pts of damage less than our 60th lvl DD. Not counting any of the new Ancient lines.<P>Now, let's look at the Wizard spell line...<P>1) Nukes. Everybody has them, we just have more, bigger, and better. With the occasional exception.<P>2) Root/Snare. We get the ability to root and or snare an enemy.<P>3) Buffs. We get the usual caster line of personal buffs, a personal damage absorbtion line, and a fire resistance buff/very weak damage shield line.<P>4) Ports. Yes, we can teleport about Norrath at whim. I play other characters as well as my wizard. Running is not that bad. (Running from Queynos to Freeport w/o SoW will take me 20 minutes, I can make the trip in 5 porting to Nro is I'm aiming for the docks.) Plus, we are generally more than happy to assist others in traveling about in the matter.<P>So, in conclusion, why are we having this discussion Mages? If anything, we should be complaining, you do the only thing that we do practically as well as we do. Plus, you get all that other neat stuff. You may not be the most mana efficient class in the game, but, you are one of the most useful, whether or not you accept it. You are the jack of all trades for this world. You do it all, but no, you are not the best at anything. If you didn't see that getting into the mage shoes, I'm sorry. I saw it, and my magi is still sitting at lvl 14 because of it. <P>I love the magician class, they're fun to play, have great RP oppurtunity, and are self reliant. The down side for me is, they are inherently easy to play. Which is why my Mage is now my alt, and my wiz is now my primary.<P>Seraphino Medsalot/Ahren<BR>27th Wizard/14th Magi<BR>Zebuxoruk<P>--------------------<P>Seraphino Medsalot<BR>31st lvl Wizard<BR>Cleric of Solusek Ro<BR>Zebuxoruk<P>Every god needs a cleric, my god just prefers to heal with fire.
</FONT>
