I personally have a real hard time with this, because my RL cousin is a epic mage and I am a epic wiz and we talk about it all the time.<P>There are quite a few comparissons you need to make here.  Singling out one situation is not going to answer any of your problems.<P>Compare soloing pre 50/after 50.<BR>Compare typical group under normal circumstances.<BR>Compare raids.<P>Soloing:  Nothing compares to AOE xp or kiting.  Wizzies have this down, but when do we become effective - post 50.  Mages have it rouger post 50, but I've watched my cousin chain cast pets and take out mobs rather effectively.  Not quite as effecient, but not bad at all.  Root is a joke, pre 24 (when we get snare) unless you have jboots.  This is where mages really have the advantage, if things go awry then can plan on the next pet or gate in worst case scenario.  Personally I'd rather gate and loose the chance at xp then get run down by a mob and loose xp.<P>Normal Groups:  Most often you are camped in a room or working your way there, and I feel that we are evenly matched.  Both have really good dmg output, whether it be DD or pet dmg.  I'd almost say mages have the upper hand considering summoning and damage shields.  We may be able to beat them to the next dungeon with ports, but thats it.  How often do you evacuate?  mana effecient or not, I almost never have this spell up.<P>Raids:  Flat out, mages get the shaft.  Pet pathing is scary at best and can really turn a raid into a nightmare.  But here is where I'm going to say, "Perform you're role".  If you had to compare the typical wiz with normal spells, not Bane spells and the amount of damage done by Damage shields, which does more damage?  Coth is great, but Verant really did the wrong thing by not activating it in all zones.  There is nothing I hate more than logging in late because of time difference and missing a raid because there is no way for me to get there.<P>Fix pet pathing and/or have the pet notify his master when it's out of LOS and this fixes a lot of problems.
